Olaide Oyelude The Katsina State Government on Saturday said bandits released a councillor, Gambo Yarliyau, his wife and one-year-old daughter. Also released from the bandits’ captivity were two unnamed indigenes of the state. The five freed victims were said to have been in bandits’ captivity for nine days. A statement by Governor Aminu Masari’s Director-General of Media, Mallam Labaran Malumfashi, in Katsina, on Saturday, confirmed the development. It was learnt that the councillor, representing Barkiya Ward in the Kurfi Local Government Area of the state, his wife and daughter were presented to the governor on  Friday evening by the Caretaker Committee Chairman of Kurfi Local Government Area, Alhaji Jabiru Tsauri. The other two freed captives, said to be traumatised, were reportedly admitted to the hospital for medical attention. The governor in the statement was quoted as saying his administration would not relent in its efforts to secure lives and property in the state. Copyright PUNCH.
